reviews_data.review_text: First time coming here and everyone was so welcoming, they were very helpful in explaining how they make their drinks, great place to get a drink

I stopped by BNKT Café in Concord on a whim after Pilates, and wow - what a treat! I ordered the Matcha Boba and it was absolutely delicious. The service was quick, friendly, and made the whole experience feel warm and welcoming. I love discovering hidden gems like this, and BNKT is definitely one I’ll be coming back to. Can’t wait to try their seasonal flavors when autumn rolls around!
very long wait, we ordered our drinks around 7:30 and only received them at 8:11. the two people behind the counter were making no progress on drinks and just letting the line get longer.

I had diarrhea because they put whole milk in my drink instead of the almond milk I asked for... also forgot my boba, but I was in a rush so I didn't say anything. I suggest that some of the employees be retrained or the hiring manager needs to do a better job. The forgetfulness happens a little too often.

I am a regular here. I go here about 2-5 times a week, so very often, and I have spent hundreds if not thousands of dollars here. Most of the time everything is okay. Today, September 5th, I went here to get drinks for me and some of my coworkers while I was on break. I bought five drinks, four of them were put in a flimsy drink carrier that they did not bother to double up to reinforce the strength of it. I thought it would be fine, but once I got into the parking garage, one of the drinks tipped out of the carrier and fell straight onto the ground and splattered open and everywhere. So, I went back, showed the workers the picture of the drink and explained what happened. All they said was around the lines of, "Ok, I'll ring it up.".. I was confused, why am I paying for the drink that I had bought for somebody else that had fallen because of their mistake and careless decision to give me four full-size drinks in a weak drink carrier? I did not drop anything on purpose.. these drinks are overpriced as is. I did not think it would be a problem for them to remake something regardless of who's fault it is if their drink or item had broken or was wrong right after purchasing it.. especially because I had just witnessed somebody, not too long ago, drop four large drinks and get them all replaced with no questions asked. I explained that to the workers, Jayden and Kayllie, as well. All they said to that was "I don't know who was there that day"... Since I was at work and on break at this time I did not have the time to argue or ask for a manager, so I decided that I was just going to pay for it since I was getting it for someone else.
How come you are able to replace other drinks for different people or mistakes that your employees make themselves but you can't do that for one of your most loyal customers.
This place is overpriced as is, even compared to other boba shops, and the fact that I come here so often and I cannot get a mistake that was on their end replaced, I am no longer going to come here.

I ordered a Mango Matcha and a Tiger Milk Tea, both with oat milk, and I clearly asked for oat milk on both. Instead, you added whole milk. My wife is dairy intolerant, and this could have seriously affected her health.

Please take more care when handling customer orders, especially when people are paying extra for dietary needs. This isn’t about just a wrong drink; it’s about respecting customers’ health.

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Faith,


Thank you for your honest feedback. We can only offer a select number of milk teas with zero sugar since the flavor comes from the tea itself instead of the sweetener we use for that drink. In our fruit teas and special teas, the flavor (strawberrry, mango, lavender, etc.) comes from the syrup we use, so if we did zero sugar, the drink would be flavorless. We apologize if this is confusing on the menu, or if no one properly explained that. 


Additionally, we apologize if our customer service was not up to par. Our customer service is our top priority, so we will be discussing this with our employees to fix this issue. We would love to make it up to you by offering you a free drink next time you visit. Email us at info@bkteacafe.com, and we can get that sorted for you. We look forward to seeing you and your daughter again! 


Thank you
-B&K Management

I am a regular here. I go here about 2-5 times a week, so very often, and I have spent hundreds if not thousands of dollars here. Most of the time everything is okay. Today, September 5th, I went here to get drinks for me and some of my coworkers while I was on break. I bought five drinks, four of them were put in a flimsy drink carrier that they did not bother to double up to reinforce the strength of it. I thought it would be fine, but once I got into the parking garage, one of the drinks tipped out of the carrier and fell straight onto the ground and splattered open and everywhere. So, I went back, showed the workers the picture of the drink and explained what happened. All they said was around the lines of, "Ok, I'll ring it up.".. I was confused, why am I paying for the drink that I had bought for somebody else that had fallen because of their mistake and careless decision to give me four full-size drinks in a weak drink carrier? I did not drop anything on purpose.. these drinks are overpriced as is. I did not think it would be a problem for them to remake something regardless of who's fault it is if their drink or item had broken or was wrong right after purchasing it.. especially because I had just witnessed somebody, not too long ago, drop four large drinks and get them all replaced with no questions asked. I explained that to the workers, Jayden and Kayllie, as well. All they said to that was "I don't know who was there that day"... Since I was at work and on break at this time I did not have the time to argue or ask for a manager, so I decided that I was just going to pay for it since I was getting it for someone else.
How come you are able to replace other drinks for different people or mistakes that your employees make themselves but you can't do that for one of your most loyal customers.
This place is overpriced as is, even compared to other boba shops, and the fact that I come here so often and I cannot get a mistake that was on their end replaced, I am no longer going to come here.
